            <div class="section"> 
  <h1>Why I&#8217;m Different</h1> 
  <h3 class="subtitle">There are a lot of designers out there. What makes me unique?</h3> 
  <div class="three_column numbered"> 
    <div class="column_1"> 
      <h4> 
        <img alt="1" class="number" height="29" src="/images/one.png" width="29" /> 
        I keep it simple
      </h4> 
      <p style="font-size: 90%"> 
        I&#8217;m in the business of making complex concepts, simple. Your website needs
        to be easy to understand and use. I&#8217;ll help you identify
        what&#8217;s important and get rid of everything else. Less is more. Really.
      </p> 
    </div> 
    <div class="column_2"> 
      <h4> 
        <img alt="2" class="number" height="29" src="/images/two.png" width="29" /> 
        I can code
      </h4> 
      <p style="font-size: 90%"> 
        Design is my specialty, but I also have a background in programming. It
        informs my design decisions and allows me to optimize my work so that your developers
        can implement it easily.
      </p> 
    </div> 
    <div class="column_3"> 
      <h4> 
        <img alt="3" class="number" height="29" src="/images/three.png" width="29" /> 
        I love business
      </h4> 
      <p style="font-size: 90%"> 
        You need someone who speaks your language. That&#8217;s me.
        I have experience helping real clients build products that make money, and I am eager
        to help you achieve success.
      </p> 
    </div> 
  </div> 
</div>

<div class="section"> 
  <h1>The Way I Work</h1> 
  <h3 class="subtitle"> 
    I use a number of tools and techniques to help clients clarify their ideas and<br /> 
    translate them into beautiful and functional products.
  </h3> 
  <div class="four_column"> 
    <div class="column_1"> 
      <h4> 
        <img alt="" class="slim-border" height="110" src="/images/client_interviews.png" width="178" /> 
        1. Client Interviews
      </h4> 
      <p style="font-size: 90%"> 
        Every project begins and ends with a series of conversations with the client. Together we
        discuss the product idea and outline how we think it will work.
      </p> 
    </div> 
    <div class="column_2"> 
      <h4> 
        <img alt="" class="slim-border" height="110" src="/images/wireframes.png" width="178" /> 
        2. Wireframes
      </h4> 
      <p style="font-size: 90%"> 
        I then make a series of quick illustrations roughing in the basic ideas.
        The point is to figure out flow and function without getting bogged down with how it
        looks.
      </p> 
    </div> 
    <div class="column_3"> 
      <h4> 
        <img alt="" class="slim-border" height="110" src="/images/mockups.png" width="178" /> 
        3. Hi-Fi Mockups
      </h4> 
      <p style="font-size: 90%"> 
        Once we have settled on the basic design, I iron out the look and feel
        with a couple of Hi-Fi mockups that show what the finished app will
        look like.
      </p> 
    </div> 
    <div class="column_4"> 
      <h4> 
        <img alt="" class="slim-border" height="110" src="/images/html_css.png" width="178" /> 
        4. HTML &amp; CSS
      </h4> 
      <p style="font-size: 90%"> 
        Finally, I convert the Hi-Fi mockups and rough wireframes into HTML and CSS. A developer
        can then use these to build the actual application.
      </p> 
    </div> 
  </div>
</div>

<div class="section narrow">
  <h1>Samples of My Work</h1>
  <h3 class="subtitle">I like happy clients. Here are a couple of my favorite projects.</h3>
  
  <table class="portfolio">
    <tr>
      <td class="image">
        <a href="#memberhub_image"><img alt="MemberHub" height="160" src="/images/portfolio/memberhub_thumbnail.jpg" width="160" /></a>
      </td>
      <td class="description">
        <h4>MemberHub.com</h4>
        <h5>Application Design &amp; Promo Site</h5>
        <p>
          In association with Adam Williams and Brandon Mathis, I led the initial design effort
          on MemberHub.com. MemberHub is a group communications and membership management tool
          targeting nonprofits and other organizations.
        </p>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td class="image">
        <a href="#ruby_lang_image"><img alt="Ruby-Lang.Org" height="160" src="/images/portfolio/ruby-lang_thumbnail.jpg" width="160" /></a>
      </td>
      <td class="description">
        <h4>The Ruby Website</h4>
        <h5>Logo, Site Design, &amp; Programming</h5>
        <p>
          As a member of the Ruby Visual Identity Team I helped redesign the website of the
          Ruby programming language. The site was the first major website to be powered by
          Radiant CMS &#8211; a content management system I created.
        </p>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td class="image">
        <a href="#pragprog_image"><img alt="Pragmatic Programmers" height="160" src="/images/portfolio/pragprog_thumbnail.jpg" width="160" /></a>
      </td>
      <td class="description">
        <h4>The Pragmatic Programmers</h4>
        <h5>Site Design</h5>
        <p>
          Dave Thomas and Andy Hunt hired me to create a template for their website <em>The Pragmatic
          Bookstore</em>. The site markets their books and screencasts to programmers and people
          involved with technology. Books are available in paper, PDF, or eBook format.
        </p>
      </td>
    </tr>
  </table>
  <p class="more"><a href="/portfolio/">View More Samples</a></p>
